sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K953006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Heme Oxygenase with T7 + Deinococcus radiodurans Bacteriophytochrome (E. coli Codon Optimised)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Daniel Winter

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K953000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Heme Oxygenase with T7 & RBS (E. coli Codon Optimised)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: E. coli codon optimised Synechocystis Heme Oxygenase with a Ribosome Binding Site (RBS) and T7 promoter (Part BBa1719005, oxidises Heme into biliverdin which absorbs light in the 360 nm and 650 nm wavelength producing a green colouration.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ryan Kenny
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The part was codon optimsed (http://www.bioinformatics.org/sms2/rev_trans.html) from Synechocystis and assembled using Gibson Assembly. Select GC rich regions were removed.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: GC rich regions, which formed hairpin loops in synthesis, were removed. Restriction sites were removed to conform to biobrick standards.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K953001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Deinococcus radiodurans Bacteriophytochrome with RBS (E. coli Codon Optimised)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Deinococcus radiodurans bacteriophytochrome, codon optimised for expression in E. coli. In the presence of biliverdin the bacteriophytochrome will undergo a conformation change. This complex can then absorb red light(620-750 nm) to excite the complex and result in a phenotypic change from blue to green. This can be reversed by far-red light (700-800 nm) or will revert from green to blue over time.
As E. coli does not produce biliverdin, heme oxygenase (Part BBa_K953000) can be coupled with this part to activate the oxidation of heme to produce biliverdin or by the addition of biliverdin to the cells.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Daniel Winter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Optimised for expression in E. coli

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K953004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Hemeoxygenase with RBS (E. coli Codon Optimised)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: E. coli codon optimised Synechocystis Heme Oxygenase with a Ribosome Binding Site (RBS), oxidises Heme into biliverdin which absorbs light in the 360 nm and 650 nm wavelength producing a green colouration.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: David Dubow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Codon optimisation for E. coli, whilst staying within the GC constraints of gibson assembly.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I712074
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: T7 promoter (strong promoter from T7 bacteriophage)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: T7 promoter is very specific promoter which is transcribed only by specific T7 RNA polymerase. Usually this promoter is used in expression systems where T7 promoter is cotransfected with T7 RNA polymerase. That ensures strong transcription of desired genes.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Rok Gaber
